WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.795 --> 00:00:02.920
<v ->Many of us can barely remember a time</v>

2
00:00:02.920 --> 00:00:04.696
when we didn't have cell phones.

3
00:00:04.696 --> 00:00:06.391
In fact, they've become such an integral

4
00:00:06.391 --> 00:00:07.958
and common part of our lives

5
00:00:07.958 --> 00:00:10.965
that we've ceased to question the technology anymore.

6
00:00:10.965 --> 00:00:12.939
One man who has not stopped questioning

7
00:00:12.939 --> 00:00:14.657
is Dr. Nick Begich.

8
00:00:14.657 --> 00:00:17.002
best known for his work in the area of HAARP,

9
00:00:17.002 --> 00:00:18.776
Dr. Begich has turned his attention

10
00:00:18.776 --> 00:00:21.040
to 21st century technologies

11
00:00:21.040 --> 00:00:22.781
and the truth behind their interface

12
00:00:22.781 --> 00:00:25.045
with the human body and brain.

13
00:00:25.045 --> 00:00:26.787
This is an interview not to be missed

14
00:00:26.787 --> 00:00:28.215
and one that you'll likely want to share

15
00:00:28.215 --> 00:00:30.833
with your family and friends.

16
00:00:41.464 --> 00:00:44.238
We're talking about 21st century technologies

17
00:00:44.238 --> 00:00:47.974
and one of the really interesting, I think fascinating,

18
00:00:47.974 --> 00:00:50.830
technologies that affect most of us now

19
00:00:50.830 --> 00:00:52.676
is cell phone technology

20
00:00:52.676 --> 00:00:54.800
and it's my understanding that some of this

21
00:00:54.800 --> 00:00:57.738
may actually be affecting us in a negative way.

22
00:00:57.738 --> 00:00:58.713
<v ->Yeah and that's right.</v>

23
00:00:58.713 --> 00:01:01.523
You know, cell phones have been one of the few devices

24
00:01:01.523 --> 00:01:03.845
that we've had in large circulation

25
00:01:03.845 --> 00:01:05.656
where we've actually taken something

26
00:01:05.656 --> 00:01:07.986
that produces a radio frequency signal

27
00:01:07.986 --> 00:01:09.925
and stuck it right next to the head.

28
00:01:09.925 --> 00:01:11.957
And you know, this created quite a bit of controversy.

29
00:01:11.957 --> 00:01:13.733
Many will remember years ago

30
00:01:13.733 --> 00:01:15.405
there was an incident in Florida

31
00:01:15.405 --> 00:01:17.971
where somebody had asserted they had a brain tumor formed

32
00:01:17.971 --> 00:01:20.897
from cell phone use and there was a lawsuit filed.

33
00:01:20.897 --> 00:01:23.312
The Congress got involved and this became

34
00:01:23.312 --> 00:01:24.403
quite the controversy

35
00:01:24.403 --> 00:01:26.841
and what happened in those congressional hearings

36
00:01:26.841 --> 00:01:31.148
eventually the industry agreed to do a $25 million study

37
00:01:31.148 --> 00:01:33.412
where they would look at cell phones

38
00:01:33.412 --> 00:01:35.223
and the literature surrounding cell phones

39
00:01:35.223 --> 00:01:37.787
and what had already been done in the research

40
00:01:37.787 --> 00:01:40.442
and try and figure out whether indeed there was

41
00:01:40.442 --> 00:01:44.889
a biological effect, an effect on our health or on our minds

42
00:01:44.889 --> 00:01:46.093
and so what happened is

43
00:01:46.093 --> 00:01:48.357
they hired a guy named Dr. George Carlo

44
00:01:48.357 --> 00:01:52.258
and Dr. Carlo put together a team of experts.

45
00:01:52.258 --> 00:01:54.963
The unusual thing was instead of reporting to

46
00:01:54.963 --> 00:01:57.111
say an engineering group or something like this

47
00:01:57.111 --> 00:02:00.339
and with the cell phone industry, his primary contact

48
00:02:00.339 --> 00:02:03.009
was our chief lobbyist in Washington, D.C.

49
00:02:03.009 --> 00:02:05.552
After five years, he completed his work,

50
00:02:05.552 --> 00:02:08.013
he produced a study.

51
00:02:08.013 --> 00:02:09.719
The industry went forward with it and said

52
00:02:09.719 --> 00:02:12.517
everything is wonderful and everything is safe

53
00:02:12.517 --> 00:02:15.792
and George Carlo was so incensed because he felt

54
00:02:15.792 --> 00:02:19.727
that there were significant problems with cell phones

55
00:02:19.727 --> 00:02:21.167
and he published a book called

56
00:02:21.167 --> 00:02:22.769
"Cell Phones: The Invisible Hazards."

57
00:02:22.769 --> 00:02:26.673
And what he showed in his theoretical model was that

58
00:02:26.673 --> 00:02:29.141
the heating that, the heat transfer from the phone

59
00:02:29.141 --> 00:02:32.612
into the head, actually caused a breakdown

60
00:02:32.612 --> 00:02:34.071
in the blood brain barrier,

61
00:02:34.071 --> 00:02:36.707
the things that separate toxins from getting into the brain

62
00:02:36.707 --> 00:02:40.550
and he felt that the most likely mechanism for tumor

63
00:02:40.550 --> 00:02:44.822
formation was in fact the slowing of the repair of DNA,

64
00:02:44.822 --> 00:02:46.215
which normally would take place,

65
00:02:46.215 --> 00:02:47.887
but by slowing it down,

66
00:02:47.887 --> 00:02:50.999
that's where the tumor formation would occur

67
00:02:50.999 --> 00:02:53.030
and that's what he felt the mechanism was.

68
00:02:53.030 --> 00:02:55.132
<v Voiceover>But you're saying that the heat transfer</v>

69
00:02:55.132 --> 00:02:58.394
was creating a slowing down of the normal DNA repair?

70
00:02:58.394 --> 00:02:59.369
<v ->That's correct.</v>

71
00:02:59.369 --> 00:03:02.341
And this slowing down is sort of the root of the problem

72
00:03:02.341 --> 00:03:04.431
in that particular incident.

73
00:03:04.431 --> 00:03:05.871
Now, what he looked at

74
00:03:05.871 --> 00:03:08.611
was he looked at children say at five years old

75
00:03:08.611 --> 00:03:12.477
and at five years old, 400% more energy

76
00:03:12.477 --> 00:03:16.285
actually transfers through the phone, through the skull

77
00:03:16.285 --> 00:03:18.119
because of skull thickness is much smaller

78
00:03:18.119 --> 00:03:20.488
in a five year old than in an adult.

79
00:03:20.488 --> 00:03:23.492
A 10 year old, 200% more energy transfers

80
00:03:23.492 --> 00:03:25.628
and then of course the adult transfer.

81
00:03:25.628 --> 00:03:27.892
Now, in Great Britain they take this into consideration.

82
00:03:27.892 --> 00:03:29.367
The beginning of the school year

83
00:03:29.367 --> 00:03:30.597
there are warnings that go out

84
00:03:30.597 --> 00:03:33.175
that tell parents if you're kids are under 16,

85
00:03:33.175 --> 00:03:35.671
you know, dissuade their use from cell phones

86
00:03:35.671 --> 00:03:37.804
because they utilize in Europe what's called

87
00:03:37.804 --> 00:03:39.279
the precautionary principle,

88
00:03:39.279 --> 00:03:41.775
which says that once you have information

89
00:03:41.775 --> 00:03:43.807
that says there may be a problem,

90
00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:45.815
you don't wait till there's absolute proof.

91
00:03:45.815 --> 00:03:48.277
You begin to give that information to the public

92
00:03:48.277 --> 00:03:49.911
so that they can utilize that information

93
00:03:49.911 --> 00:03:50.781
in making decisions.

94
00:03:50.781 --> 00:03:53.487
Now, this applies to areas in health

95
00:03:53.487 --> 00:03:54.996
and areas within the environment

96
00:03:54.996 --> 00:03:57.654
and this principle's been applied in Europe about 30 years

97
00:03:57.654 --> 00:04:00.499
and never once have they been wrong,

98
00:04:00.499 --> 00:04:03.436
not waiting for this final proof of the studies

99
00:04:03.436 --> 00:04:04.737
like we do in the United States.

100
00:04:04.737 --> 00:04:06.768
Now, there's been several other studies

101
00:04:06.768 --> 00:04:07.999
beyond George Carlo's.

102
00:04:07.999 --> 00:04:10.031
There was one study that we actually cite

103
00:04:10.031 --> 00:04:11.665
in some of our work

104
