00:20:38.288 --> 00:20:40.622
and they do it with the establishment first

524
00:20:40.622 --> 00:20:41.992
of what are called dictionaries.

525
00:20:41.992 --> 00:20:44.093
Now, dictionaries as you and I think about them

526
00:20:44.093 --> 00:20:46.502
are little books with words in them.

527
00:20:46.502 --> 00:20:48.232
The way these agencies think about them

528
00:20:48.232 --> 00:20:50.867
is it's that plus word phrases,

529
00:20:50.867 --> 00:20:53.213
voice information, voice print information.

530
00:20:53.213 --> 00:20:55.209
You know when Osama bin Laden goes on the phone

531
00:20:55.209 --> 00:20:57.404
and they say, or does a press conference

532
00:20:57.404 --> 00:20:58.681
that they try and interpret,

533
00:20:58.681 --> 00:20:59.981
they say it takes weeks to figure out.

534
00:20:59.981 --> 00:21:01.746
It doesn't, it takes seconds.

535
00:21:01.746 --> 00:21:03.685
They know immediately who it is.

536
00:21:03.685 --> 00:21:05.647
That's why he got rid of all forms

537
00:21:05.647 --> 00:21:09.188
of electronic communication before he hit the trail

538
00:21:09.188 --> 00:21:10.488
and that's why we can't find him.

539
00:21:10.488 --> 00:21:13.298
There's no electronic signature to go after

540
00:21:13.298 --> 00:21:15.759
because he's not on the grid so to speak.

541
00:21:15.759 --> 00:21:18.267
By the same token, when you look at

542
00:21:18.267 --> 00:21:21.564
sort of the invasiveness of all this and where it heads,

543
00:21:21.564 --> 00:21:23.433
there was a paper put together, it was called

544
00:21:23.433 --> 00:21:25.010
"The Revolution in Military Affairs

545
00:21:25.010 --> 00:21:28.114
"and Conflict Short of War" and it was 1989 or '90

546
00:21:28.114 --> 00:21:30.007
by the U.S. Army War College

547
00:21:30.007 --> 00:21:33.385
and it was, you know, that's a really good institution

548
00:21:33.385 --> 00:21:36.183
in terms of laying doctrine out for military training

549
00:21:36.183 --> 00:21:37.588
and leaders that are coming.

550
00:21:37.588 --> 00:21:40.491
And they looked at all of these technologies

551
00:21:40.491 --> 00:21:45.065
and much, much more as a change that was so profound

552
00:21:45.065 --> 00:21:46.319
in terms of what was happening.

553
00:21:46.319 --> 00:21:48.722
They equated the changes in military technologies

554
00:21:48.722 --> 00:21:52.368
from the days of gunpowder being introduced

555
00:21:52.368 --> 00:21:53.691
into Europe in the Middle Ages

556
00:21:53.691 --> 00:21:56.269
or that atomic weapons of the last century,

557
00:21:56.269 --> 00:21:59.009
those are the kind of changes that they say are coming

558
00:21:59.009 --> 00:22:01.342
based on electromagnetic systems

559
00:22:01.342 --> 00:22:03.711
for surveillance and offensive weaponry.

560
00:22:03.711 --> 00:22:06.346
So when you talk about sort of where does it go,

561
00:22:06.346 --> 00:22:07.681
what they said in this

562
00:22:07.681 --> 00:22:09.655
was there were several things that we could do

563
00:22:09.655 --> 00:22:13.544
that would increase our capacity as a country militarily,

564
00:22:13.544 --> 00:22:16.354
but these things would run counter to American values.

565
00:22:16.354 --> 00:22:18.629
One of the examples that was given within this paper

566
00:22:18.629 --> 00:22:20.824
was microchip technology

567
00:22:20.824 --> 00:22:22.728
that could be embedded in service personnel

568
00:22:22.728 --> 00:22:25.828
that would be used in '89 and '90 for just GPS,

569
00:22:25.828 --> 00:22:27.894
for locating them in the battlefield.

570
00:22:27.894 --> 00:22:30.274
And you know, if you were going in the battlefield

571
00:22:30.274 --> 00:22:31.238
you might want that.

572
00:22:31.238 --> 00:22:33.212
I mean, if you were going in and you got captured

573
00:22:33.212 --> 00:22:35.371
or got hurt and you wanted to be extracted

574
00:22:35.371 --> 00:22:38.413
and found rapidly, you know, this would be ideal.

575
00:22:38.413 --> 00:22:41.013
So in that sense, if you had a vote on it,

576
00:22:41.013 --> 00:22:42.813
that would be great, but as we know in the military

577
00:22:42.813 --> 00:22:44.276
you don't get votes, you get orders

578
00:22:44.276 --> 00:22:46.157
so everybody does what they're told.

579
00:22:46.157 --> 00:22:48.107
The problem is they didn't stop there.

580
00:22:48.107 --> 00:22:49.651
They suggested that this be installed

581
00:22:49.651 --> 00:22:52.658
in every business traveler because it's a volatile world,

582
00:22:52.658 --> 00:22:54.597
but don't worry, they won't turn them on

583
00:22:54.597 --> 00:22:57.337
unless there's a problem is what they said.

584
00:22:57.337 --> 00:23:00.205
The problem with all of that is it really runs counter

585
00:23:00.205 --> 00:23:04.195
to how Americans and most free peoples feel

586
00:23:04.195 --> 00:23:06.912
about their government's ability to monitor activity,

587
00:23:06.912 --> 00:23:09.245
although already in the Attorney General's office

588
00:23:09.245 --> 00:23:13.646
in Mexico City, they have installed 200 people

589
00:23:13.646 --> 00:23:15.584
with microcircuits to track their movements.

590
00:23:15.584 --> 00:23:20.584
This was major media in the last year, has come out,

591
00:23:20.623 --> 00:23:23.758
and they'd like to have their entire bureaucracy chipped

592
00:23:23.758 --> 00:23:24.988
for tracking purposes.

593
00:23:24.988 --> 00:23:27.868
The places it also comes up is with elders

594
00:23:27.868 --> 00:23:30.526
who are losing mental faculties for keeping track of them,

595
00:23:30.526 --> 00:23:33.359
children because of fear of kidnapping,

596
00:23:33.359 --> 00:23:35.774
prisoners on parole instead of ankle bracelets,

597
00:23:35.774 --> 00:23:37.574
sex offenders for life so you can track

598
00:23:37.574 --> 00:23:40.047
where they're at, where they've been all their lives.

599
00:23:40.047 --> 00:23:41.974
And many people would go, "You know,

600
00:23:41.974 --> 00:23:45.214
"those would be alright applications," at least today.

601
00:23:45.214 --> 00:23:49.614
Pre 9/11, nobody believed that.

602
00:23:49.614 --> 00:23:51.088
<v Voiceover>Right, that's true.</v>

603
00:23:51.088 --> 00:23:54.188
And so now the government can have the media

604
00:23:54.188 --> 00:23:55.187
throw up an orange alert

605
00:23:55.187 --> 00:23:57.462
and everybody says, "I'll do it, I'll do it."

606
00:23:57.462 --> 00:23:58.124
Is that what's going on?

607
00:23:58.124 --> 00:23:59.459
<v ->That's exactly what's going on</v>

608
00:23:59.459 --> 00:24:01.630
and here's what this paper said.

609
00:24:01.630 --> 00:24:04.370
This paper projected that the only way

610
00:24:04.370 --> 00:24:06.831
that these technologies and many others that they referenced

611
00:24:06.831 --> 00:24:10.268
could be advanced, would be a change in American values.

612
00:24:10.268 --> 00:24:12.811
And they believe that the only way those values would change

613
00:24:12.811 --> 00:24:15.980
is in an environment of fear stimulated by two things:

614
00:24:15.980 --> 00:24:17.408
international terrorism

615
00:24:17.408 --> 00:24:19.146
and in international drug trafficking.

616
00:24:19.146 --> 00:24:19.947
<v Voiceover>When was this written?</v>

617
00:24:19.947 --> 00:24:21.178
<v ->'89.</v>

618
00:24:21.178 --> 00:24:22.176
'89 or '90.

619
00:24:22.176 --> 00:24:24.522
But in any case, you can see it referenced in our work

620
00:24:24.522 --> 00:24:26.414
and the point of the matter is

621
00:24:26.414 --> 00:24:28.887
look at what's happened since 9/11.

622
00:24:28.887 --> 00:24:31.488
Look at the PSAs, the public service announcements,

623
00:24:31.488 --> 00:24:34.495
that tie drug trafficking and terrorism together,

624
00:24:34.495 --> 00:24:37.304
you know, that start to amplify that kind of fear.

625
00:24:37.304 --> 00:24:39.231
One of the things in that paper that it said

626
00:24:39.231 --> 00:24:41.762
that was highly disturbing was the idea that

627
00:24:41.762 --> 00:24:43.570
we could use this intelligence

628
00:24:43.570 --> 00:24:46.078
and maybe combine it with other technologies

629
00:24:46.078 --> 00:24:47.808
and knock an aircraft out of the sky

630
00:24:47.808 --> 00:24:50.745
that was carrying suspected terrorists, for example.

631
00:24:50.745 --> 00:24:53.311
So we'd knock it out of the sky, it'd crash,

632
00:24:53.311 --> 00:24:54.449
and when you looked at all of it

633
00:24:54.449 --> 00:24:56.109
it would look like pilot error.

634
00:24:56.109 --> 00:24:57.676
And the argument was made that maybe

635
00:24:57.676 --> 00:24:59.882
the Constitution stopped at the doorstep

636
00:24:59.882 --> 00:25:03.156
of the United States and didn't carry beyond our boundaries.

637
00:25:03.156 --> 00:25:05.293
Now, there's nobody that I have met

638
00:25:05.293 --> 00:25:07.057
along the road of life that believes

639
00:25:07.057 --> 00:25:10.262
that our military drops the Constitution at the door.

640
00:25:10.262 --> 00:25:12.804
Quite the contrary, it goes with them.

641
00:25:12.804 --> 00:25:14.066
Those are the values that we expect them

642
00:25:14.066 --> 00:25:15.668
to carry, not forget.

643
00:25:15.668 --> 00:25:17.770
Now, this was actually, it actually happened,

644
00:25:17.770 --> 00:25:20.278
that the NSA provided the Peruvian Air Force,

645
00:25:20.278 --> 00:25:23.215
less than a year ago, information and intelligence

646
00:25:23.215 --> 00:25:26.477
on a drug trafficking air craft.

647
00:25:26.477 --> 00:25:28.846
The Peruvian Air Force went up, shot the air craft down

648
00:25:28.846 --> 00:25:30.947
and it contained a couple of missionaries,

649
00:25:30.947 --> 00:25:33.083
not drug traffickers at all.

650
00:25:33.083 --> 00:25:35.080
So the problem they predicted could happen,

651
00:25:35.080 --> 00:25:37.286
which is downing the wrong air craft,

652
00:25:37.286 --> 00:25:39.562
did happen and there was no deniability.

653
00:25:39.562 --> 00:25:41.466
The United States was culpable,

654
00:25:41.466 --> 00:25:43.765
but nobody's been held responsible.

655
00:25:43.765 --> 00:25:46.330
So we are already engaged in the violation

656
00:25:46.330 --> 00:25:48.467
of our own sense of right and wrong because

657
00:25:48.467 --> 00:25:52.135
all these things violate basic constitutional previsions

658
00:25:52.135 --> 00:25:54.411
like a presumption of innocence,

659
00:25:54.411 --> 00:25:58.295
a jury, a judge, and an outcome.

660
00:25:59.914 --> 00:26:04.914
<v Voiceover>Well, none of it sounds to bode well right now.</v>

661
00:26:04.953 --> 00:26:08.424
From a consumer, an advocate, point of view

662
00:26:08.424 --> 00:26:09.991
what can the average person do

663
00:26:09.991 --> 00:26:14.498
in terms of protecting themselves in any way?

664
00:26:14.498 --> 00:26:15.926
Other than not having a cell phone,

665
00:26:15.926 --> 00:26:17.700
but it sounds like that's really just

666
00:26:17.700 --> 00:26:19.499
a drop in the large bucket

667
00:26:19.499 --> 00:26:22.994
where these invasions of our personal rights

668
00:26:22.994 --> 00:26:24.198
seem to be taking place.

669
00:26:24.198 --> 00:26:27.031
<v ->Absolutely, you know, the key elements are several.</v>

670
00:26:27.031 --> 00:26:29.248
Firstly, you know, the idea of educating the public

671
00:26:29.248 --> 00:26:30.873
on what these technologies do.

672
00:26:30.873 --> 00:26:33.381
Technology generally doubles about every 10 months,

673
00:26:33.381 --> 00:26:35.645
from the invention of the wheel to where we are today.

674
00:26:35.645 --> 00:26:38.048
So it becomes extremely important

675
00:26:38.048 --> 00:26:40.858
that technological issues get some public debate.

676
00:26:40.858 --> 00:26:43.180
One of the roles that we played in the last 11 years

677
00:26:43.180 --> 00:26:46.593
is to try and force that debate, to bring information out,

678
00:26:46.593 --> 00:26:49.020
working with over 200 radio and TV producers

679
00:26:49.020 --> 00:26:50.668
around the world,

680
00:26:50.668 --> 00:26:53.107
we continue to take the information forward,

681
00:26:53.107 --> 00:26:55.928
build our databases and get the information out,

682
00:26:55.928 --> 00:26:58.169
hoping that we could see the political changes

683
00:26:58.169 --> 00:27:00.537
that are necessary to properly regulate

684
00:27:00.537 --> 00:27:02.337
and protect the values that Americans

685
00:27:02.337 --> 00:27:05.413
and other free peoples around the world hold in common.

686
00:27:05.413 --> 00:27:07.851
And that ultimately is the first step

687
00:27:07.851 --> 00:27:08.780
in the right direction.

688
00:27:08.780 --> 00:27:12.205
It has to be education followed by political action

689
00:27:12.205 --> 00:27:14.527
that restrains and constrains industry

690
00:27:14.527 --> 00:27:17.464
from abusing power that technology today offers.

691
00:27:17.464 --> 00:27:20.088
And you know, in all of our work what we have found

692
00:27:20.088 --> 00:27:24.024
is the abuses of technology, the abuses of power,

693
00:27:24.024 --> 00:27:26.334
are not based on some sinister viewpoint

694
00:27:26.334 --> 00:27:29.237
held by a few, but based on the concepts

695
00:27:29.237 --> 00:27:31.036
that their ideas are important,

696
00:27:31.036 --> 00:27:32.511
they want to further their ideas

697
00:27:32.511 --> 00:27:34.345
and they're using technology to do it.

698
00:27:34.345 --> 00:27:37.283
And sometimes people get a little zealous (laughs)

699
00:27:37.283 --> 00:27:39.314
and I think whether you're from the left or the right,

700
00:27:39.314 --> 00:27:40.510
the temptation.

701
00:27:40.510 --> 00:27:42.751
Zbigniew Brzezinski said it in "Between Two Ages,"

702
00:27:42.751 --> 00:27:44.376
a book he wrote in the early '70s,

703
00:27:44.376 --> 00:27:46.106
before he was National Security Advisor

704
00:27:46.106 --> 00:27:49.357
to Jimmy Carter, that as these technologies evolved

705
00:27:49.357 --> 00:27:51.458
that the left or the right would be tempted to use them

706
00:27:51.458 --> 00:27:52.991
to further their political ends

707
00:27:52.991 --> 00:27:54.558
and I think that's what we're seeing

708
00:27:54.558 --> 00:27:57.054
is these technologies are being used

709
00:27:57.054 --> 00:28:00.604
not just for political purposes, but for many purposes

710
00:28:00.604 --> 00:28:03.541
under the illusion of creating safety and security,

711
00:28:03.541 --> 00:28:07.338
but what are we creating that safety and security for

712
00:28:07.338 --> 00:28:09.729
if it's not to maintain those basic values

713
00:28:09.729 --> 00:28:11.842
that have been the American character,

714
00:28:11.842 --> 00:28:14.849
that have been who we are as human beings?

715
00:28:14.849 --> 00:28:18.068
And that's what's missing in the equation.

